# {{context|music}} A special [[tremolo]] effect on the [[harp]] where a [[chord]] or [[note]] is rapidly repeated at a low [[volume]]. Usually, the effect is achieved by both hands playing adjacent strings set to the same [[pitch]]es and can sound like strumming a [[guitar]] or "[[watery]]". On [[sheet music]], it is represented by three thick lines connecting the notes to be trilled.

